main event: An unidentified object was sighted by police officers in Westland, Michigan on August 21, 1969.
interesting points: The object was described as having distinctive coloring and lighting effects.
The object was observed for a period of time by the officers.
Another smaller tri-color object approached the first object and then moved out of sight within approximately 2 minutes.
The officers were unable to determine the cause or identity of the objects.
The Air Force requested the witness to complete an AF Form 117 for further investigation.
sighted object: an unidentified object with distinctive coloring and lighting, and a smaller tri-color object
photographs: no photographs included in the case file
